tags.description: A 150-foot-long overgrown dirt path leading down to a cobble beach and a small breakwater. It is possible to walk a short distance down the beach in either direction. “No Parking” signs are posted on both sides of the street.
tags.name: Low Lane Public Access

tags.description: This right-of-way provides access to a small beach via a ramp through the seawall at the end of the road. It is located between the Coast Guard station on the south and a carpet factory and Elks Lodge on the north. 2 hour parking on Thames Street.
tags.name: Constitution Street Public Access

tags.description: This 40-foot-wide right-of-way with a grassy area and benches. It leads down to a seawall and a ramp walkway to a sand and gravel beach. This site is ideal for wading and for viewing the harbor and boats.
tags.name: Union Street Public Access
